Class TimingGraph

  • Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, org.jgrapht.Graph<TimingVertex,TimingEdge>

    public class TimingGraph
extends org.jgrapht.graph.DefaultDirectedWeightedGraph<TimingVertex,TimingEdge>
    A TimingGraph is an acyclic weighted-directed graph representing logic delays and physical net delays based on analyzing the circuits within Design objects.

      • superSource

        public TimingVertex superSource
        The superSource and superSink are used to consolidate all timing start and end points, respectively. They simplify timing computations and data to compute clock skew will be annotated on the edges from superSource and to superSink. For example, a FF will be represented both as a start and end points using two vertices, says source and sink. The superSource will have no input, but fanout to all the start points nodes. The superSink will have fanin from all the end point nodes and have no output.
